    Thu 09 Oct 00:01:10 2008 | | Sponsored Links Smoke in Hercules engine sparks alert Oct 6, 2008 3:18 PM Smoke coming from the engine of a Defence Force C-130 Hercules aircraft sparked an alert at Christchurch International Airport early on Monday afternoon. The plane had just landed after a test flight when smoke was noticed coming from one of the engines. Christchurch International Airport spokesperson Chelsea Halliwell said the fire was contained by airport staff before emergency services arrived at the scene. No one was hurt during the incident and the cause of the fire was being investigated. Source: NZPA Share Headlines 